<!-- 定義與病徵 -->
'''-{zh-hant:發燒;zh-tw:發燒;zh-hk:發燒;zh-hans:发烧;zh-cn:发烧}-'''（{{lang-en|fever}}），又稱作為'''發熱'''（{{lang-en|pyrexia}}）或'''發燒反應'''（{{lang-en|febrile response}}）<ref name=NC08>{{cite journal |author=Axelrod YK, Diringer MN |title=Temperature management in acute neurologic disorders |journal=Neurol Clin |volume=26 |issue=2 |pages=585–603, xi |date=2008年5月 |pmid=18514828 |doi=10.1016/j.ncl.2008.02.005 |url=|last2=Diringer }}</ref>，其定義為：[[人體溫度|體溫]]在[[體溫調節|調節]]時超過了[[人體溫度|平常體溫]]。<ref name=Kl2015>{{cite book|last=Kluger|first=Matthew J.|title=Fever: Its Biology, Evolution, and Function|date=2015|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=9781400869831|page=57|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gIF9BgAAQBAJ&pg=PA57}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Fever: Its Biology, Evolution, and Function|date=2015|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=9781400869831|page=57|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=gIF9BgAAQBAJ&pg=PA57|access-date=2017-07-16|archive-date=2016-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160514030231/https://books.google.ca/books?id=gIF9BgAAQBAJ&pg=PA57|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=Gar2012p375>{{cite book|last1=Garmel|first1=Fever in adultsGus M.|title=An introduction to clinical emergency medicine|date=2012|publisher=Cambridge University Press|location=Cambridge|isbn=0521747767|pages=375|edition=2nd|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=pyAlcOfBhjIC&lpg=PP1&dq=An%20Introduction%20to%20Clinical%20Emergency%20Medicine&pg=PA375|access-date=2017-07-16|archive-date=2017-08-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803091638/https://books.google.ca/books?id=pyAlcOfBhjIC&lpg=PP1&dq=An%20Introduction%20to%20Clinical%20Emergency%20Medicine&pg=PA375|dead-url=no}}</ref>現在醫界並沒有一致認可的正常體溫上限，文獻從37.3到38.3℃都有。<ref name=NC08/><ref name=CC09>{{cite journal |author=Laupland KB |title=Fever in the critically ill medical patient |journal=Crit.Care Med.|volume=37 |issue=7 Suppl |pages=S273–8 |date=July 2009 |pmid=19535958 |doi=10.1097/CCM.0b013e3181aa6117 }}</ref>[[下視丘|下視丘]]的體溫調節中心將原本的體溫設定（set point）調高，即為发烧，并讓人感到寒冷。<ref name=Peds2011/>這使得身體為了生產更多熱而出現{{tsl|en|muscle tone||肌肉收縮}}，且開始試圖保存熱量。<ref name=Sue2014/>當体温调定点回到正常值时（即為退燒時），患者就會開始感到燥熱，出現{{tsl|en|flushed|臉紅|臉紅}}，也可能開始[[汗液|流汗]]。<ref name=Sue2014>{{cite book|author1=Sue E. Huether|title=Pathophysiology: The Biologic Basis for Disease in Adults and Children|date=2014|publisher=Elsevier Health Sciences|isbn=9780323293754|page=498|edition=7|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=l9XsAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA498|access-date=2017-07-16|archive-date=2017-08-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803092406/https://books.google.ca/books?id=l9XsAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA498|dead-url=no}}</ref>發燒導致的[[熱性痙攣|熱性痙攣]]（較強烈的肌肉收縮）較為少見，<!-- <ref name=CDC2010/> -->然而這在年輕孩童患者之中較為常見。<ref name=CDC2010>{{cite web |title=Taking Care of Someone Who is Sick |url=http://www.cdc.gov/flu/homecare/treatfever.htm |archivedate=2015-03-24 |accessdate=2017-02-09 |date=2010-08-13 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150324084355/http://www.cdc.gov/flu/homecare/treatfever.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>發燒通常不會高到{{convert|41|to|42|C|F|1}}<ref name=Gar2012p375/><ref name=Peds2011/>。

<!-- 原因 -->
'''發燒'''是指身體製造過多熱能或身體的[[體溫調節|體溫調節]]失調，導致身體的溫度高過溫度設定值或溫度設定值本身過高。<ref name=NC08/>發燒可能是由許多[[疾病|疾病]]造成，從[[生病|小病]]到[[重症照護醫學|重症]]都有可能，<!-- <ref name=Gar2012p5/> -->這包含了[[病毒感染|病毒]]、[[病原細菌|細菌]]、[[寄生|寄生]]、[[普通感冒|普通感冒]]、[[流行感冒|流行感冒]]、[[泌尿道感染|泌尿道感染]]、[[脑膜炎|脑膜炎]]、[[疟疾|疟疾]]、[[闌尾炎|闌尾炎]]等。<!-- <ref name=Gar2012p5/> --> 非感染性的發燒成因包含了[[血管炎|血管炎]]、[[深静脉血栓|深静脉血栓]]、[[副作用|藥物的副作用]]、[[癌症|癌症]]等。<ref name=Gar2012p5>{{cite book|last1=Garmel|first1=Fever in adultsGus M.|title=An introduction to clinical emergency medicine|date=2012|publisher=Cambridge University Press|location=Cambridge|isbn=0521747767|pages=5|edition=2nd|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=pyAlcOfBhjIC&lpg=PP1&dq=An%20Introduction%20to%20Clinical%20Emergency%20Medicine&pg=PA5|access-date=2017-07-17|archive-date=2017-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021221058/https://books.google.ca/books?id=pyAlcOfBhjIC&lpg=PP1&dq=An%20Introduction%20to%20Clinical%20Emergency%20Medicine&pg=PA5|dead-url=no}}</ref>另外，發燒不等同[[高熱|高熱]]這個類似疾病，不同之處在於，[[高熱|高熱]]（[[中暑|中暑]]為[[高熱|高熱]]的一種<ref name=EMS>{{cite book |title=Emergency Medicine: A Comprehensive Study Guide, Sixth edition |last=Tintinalli |first=Judith  |year=2004 |publisher=McGraw-Hill Professional |location= |isbn=0-07-138875-3 |page=1187 |url= }}</ref><ref name=H>{{cite book
